==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|tyhtan|lang=ang}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈtaɪ.tən/}}
* {{rhymes|aɪtən}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To make [[tight]]er.
#: ''Please '''tighten''' that screw a quarter-turn.''
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To become tighter.
#: ''That joint is '''tightening''' as the wood dries.''
# {{context|economics|lang=en}} To make money harder to borrow or obtain.
#: ''If the government doesn't '''tighten''' the money supply, inflation is certain to be harsh.''
# {{context|economics|lang=en}} To raise short-term interest rates.
#: ''The Fed is expected to '''tighten''' by a quarter-point.''

